[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     29[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe recipe correctly identifies that the BAA must be signed before processing patient messages. The non-negotiable human-in-the-loop design is the right safety posture. Bedrock Guardrails as a secondary safety layer (after the system prompt as primary) is architecturally sound. The prerequisites table covers encryption at rest (S3 SSE-KMS, DynamoDB default), TLS in transit, CloudTrail, and model invocation logging. The explicit "Never use real patient messages in dev" warning is good.[K
