[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     48[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The prerequisites state "DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default)." Default DynamoDB encryption uses AWS-owned keys, which do not appear in CloudTrail and cannot be revoked. For a table storing patient messages, draft responses, and clinical context (all PHI), most healthcare compliance programs require customer-managed KMS keys for auditability and key lifecycle control.[K
