[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    33[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe regime catalog is the substrate of the system.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m State definitions, action catalogs, reward functions, decision-point cadences, eligibility predicates, and model risk tiers are the artifacts the rest of the pipeline operates on. This example ships a small synthetic regime covering diabetes / CKD stepwise therapy with a five-action catalog (add an SGLT2, intensify the GLP-1, add basal insulin, add a DPP-4, no change). Production maintains many regimes per clinical area, with cohort overrides, evidence references, versioning, and a regime-governance committee that approves promotions.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    34[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mOff-policy evaluation is the load-bearing inference, not a sanity check.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The OPE estimators (doubly-robust, importance sampling, fitted Q evaluation) plus the sensitivity analysis are what produce a value estimate with confidence intervals that the governance committee actually cares about. The example computes all three estimators and a simple E-value-style sensitivity analysis, with cohort stratification.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    35[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe four-layer validator from Recipes 4.5 through 4.9 carries forward.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Schema and length, fact grounding, prohibited-language patterns, and required content. The regime-narrative-specific prohibited-language patterns are stricter (no policy-as-directive framing, no recommendation language that elides alternatives, no probabilistic claims framed as guarantees, explicit override-encouragement framing required).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    36[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBedrock model IDs change over time.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some regions require cross-region inference profile IDs (prefixed [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mus.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140meu.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The IDs below are reasonable defaults; verify in the Bedrock console for your region before running.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    37[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAll patients, trajectories, actions, narratives, and outcomes in the example are synthetic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Do not treat any specific patient_id, trajectory_id, recommendation_id, or narrative as real. A production system ingests from real EHR, FHIR, claims, lab, pharmacy, and registry feeds under BAA.[K
